Program: Great Lives
Title: Douglas Jardine
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00s0d1g
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 17 Nov 2017
The controversial England cricket captain, Douglas Jardine, who was responsible for the infamous 1932 Bodyline tour of Australia, is Peter White's chioce of a Great Life. Matthew Parris, who is sceptical about cricket to say the least, presents, while Christopher Douglas (who co-writes and presents Ed Reardon on Radio 4, the disaffected, failed 50-something hack writer) fills in the biographical gaps. Producer: Mark Smalley. Show less